The paper deals with image matching using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Siamese convolutional neural networks also suggests that the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel hybrid approach, which involves combining traditional descriptors with deep learning techniques, indicating that it may also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The evaluation of the proposed approach on two datasets, one of which involves 3D projective transformations, suggests that the paper may also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
